{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-js","path":"/projects/personal-site/","webpackCompilationHash":"1d22558e4fe95a6ecbe7","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"b6f07f4e-3dc6-5a6a-b4b5-fb10b5188154","excerpt":"My personal portfolio website built with Gatsby.js. A fun venture into the JAM stack and a constant work-in-progress.Rather than go off of an existing portfolioâ€¦","html":"<p>My personal portfolio website built with <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/\">Gatsby.js</a>. A fun venture into the JAM stack and a constant work-in-progress.</p>\n<p>Rather than go off of an existing portfolio template or starter-site, this project was started with a bare-bones Gatsby site and built up from there. The site is currently deployed with GitHub pages <a href=\"https://billybunn.com/\">here</a>.</p>\n<h3>Features</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Site pages programmatically created from different data sources with GraphQL and assigned different page templates (see <a href=\"https://github.com/BillyBunn/billybunn.github.io/blob/development/gatsby-node.js\"><code>gatsby-node.js</code></a> where this configuration was made)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Site pages (e.g., <code>billybunn.com/about</code>) are programmatically created with <code>.js</code> files in the <code>pages/</code> folder (as with most Gatsby sites)</li>\n<li>Project pages (e.g., <code>billybunn.com/projects/my-project</code>) are programmatically created from markdown files</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Pagination between project pages</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/BillyBunn/billybunn.github.io/blob/development/src/components/tab-filter/tab-filter.js\"><code>TabFilter</code> component</a> for displaying projects and filtering based on custom tags. This component allowed for a much cleaner API on <a href=\"https://github.com/BillyBunn/billybunn.github.io/blob/development/src/pages/projects.js\">the <code>/projects</code> page</a> where content is populated by a static GraphQL query.</li>\n<li>Responsive header rendering with a custom <code>useWindowSize</code> React hook</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/BillyBunn/billybunn.github.io/blob/development/src/components/header/mobile-header/mobile-header.js\"><code>MobileHeader</code></a> menu component that closes on click outside using custom <code>onClickOutside</code> React hook</li>\n<li>CSS-in-JS styling with Styled Components</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/BillyBunn/billybunn.github.io\">See project source code on GitHub</a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b7949efaf6dcfb003ceb367be3aa81d5/a6f9d/personal-site-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 98.6910994764398%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"personal website home page\"\n        title=\"personal website home page\"\n        src=\"/static/b7949efaf6dcfb003ceb367be3aa81d5/b9e4f/personal-site-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b7949efaf6dcfb003ceb367be3aa81d5/cf440/personal-site-1.png 148w,\n/static/b7949efaf6dcfb003ceb367be3aa81d5/d2d38/personal-site-1.png 295w,\n/static/b7949efaf6dcfb003ceb367be3aa81d5/b9e4f/personal-site-1.png 590w,\n/static/b7949efaf6dcfb003ceb367be3aa81d5/f9b6a/personal-site-1.png 885w,\n/static/b7949efaf6dcfb003ceb367be3aa81d5/2d849/personal-site-1.png 1180w,\n/static/b7949efaf6dcfb003ceb367be3aa81d5/a6f9d/personal-site-1.png 1528w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Resources and References</h3>\n<p>Inspiration and direction for certain features was gathered from the sources credited below.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/tutorial/\">Official Gatsby.js Tutorial</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/starters/gatsbyjs/gatsby-starter-blog/\">Gatsby Starter Blog</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/starters/fabe/gatsby-universal/\">Gatsby Starter Universal</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@rossbulat/creating-themes-in-react-with-styled-components-6fce744b4e54\">Theming in React with Styled Components</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/simplifying-responsive-layouts-with-react-hooks-19db73893a7a\">Simplifying Responsive Layouts with React Hooks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://chipcullen.com/making-multiple-content-types-in-gatsby/\">Making a Gatsby Site with Multiple Content Types</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://usehooks.com/\">useHooks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/simplifying-responsive-layouts-with-react-hooks-19db73893a7a\">A gentle Introduction to React's Higher Order Components</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Personal Website","date":"July 07, 2019","description":"My personal Gatsby.js website listing my projects.","source":"https://github.com/BillyBunn/billybunn.github.io","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.022636484687084,"src":"/static/202788c508a222e3155b6a281343b394/af150/personal-site-2.png","srcSet":"/static/202788c508a222e3155b6a281343b394/52912/personal-site-2.png 128w,\n/static/202788c508a222e3155b6a281343b394/5e640/personal-site-2.png 256w,\n/static/202788c508a222e3155b6a281343b394/af150/personal-site-2.png 511w,\n/static/202788c508a222e3155b6a281343b394/afae4/personal-site-2.png 767w,\n/static/202788c508a222e3155b6a281343b394/ae597/personal-site-2.png 1023w,\n/static/202788c508a222e3155b6a281343b394/c5131/personal-site-2.png 1536w","srcWebp":"/static/202788c508a222e3155b6a281343b394/88b22/personal-site-2.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/202788c508a222e3155b6a281343b39